\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/117/263/s3543/a/5"},"text":"Pub. L. 117–263, § 3543(a)(5)","children":[],"tail":", redesignated subsec. (e) as (b). Former subsec. (b) redesignated (a)(2)."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/117/263/s3543/a/2/B"},"text":"Pub. L. 117–263, § 3543(a)(2)(B)","children":[],"tail":", redesignated pars. (1) and (2) as subpars. (A) and (B), respectively, and realigned margins."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Subsec. (b)(1). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/117/263/s3543/a/2/A"},"text":"Pub. L. 117–263, § 3543(a)(2)(A)","children":[],"tail":", redesignated subpars. (A) to (D) as cls. (i) to (iv), respectively, realigned margins, and substituted “incidental vessel-generated underwater noise, such as noise from propeller cavitation or hydrodynamic flow” for “propeller cavitation” in cl. (iv)."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Subsec. (c). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/117/263/s3543/a/9"},"text":"Pub. L. 117–263, § 3543(a)(9)","children":[],"tail":", added subsec. (c). Former subsec. (c) redesignated (a)(3)."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/117/263/s3543/a/3"},"text":"Pub. L. 117–263, § 3543(a)(3)","children":[],"tail":", redesignated pars. (1) and (2) as subpars. (A) and (B), respectively, and realigned margins."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Subsec. (d). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/117/263/s3543/a/9"},"text":"Pub. L. 117–263, § 3543(a)(9)","children":[],"tail":", added subsec. (d). Former subsec. (d) redesignated (a)(4)."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Subsec. (e). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/117/263/s3543/a/9"},"text":"Pub. L. 117–263, § 3543(a)(9)","children":[],"tail":", added subsec. (e). Former subsec. (e) redesignated (b)."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Subsec. (f). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/117/263/s3543/a/6"},"text":"Pub. L. 117–263, § 3543(a)(6)","children":[],"tail":", struck out subsec. (f). Text read as follows: “Not more than three percent of the funds appropriated to carry out this section may be used for administrative purposes.”"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"2021—Subsec. (a). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/116/283"},"text":"Pub. L. 116–283","children":[],"tail":" substituted “maritime transportation” for “marine transportation”."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Subsecs. (e), (f). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/117/81"},"text":"Pub. L. 117–81","children":[],"tail":" added subsec. (e) and redesignated former subsec. (e) as (f)."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"2019—Subsec. (a). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/116/92/s3503/1"},"text":"Pub. L. 116–92, § 3503(1)","children":[],"tail":", substituted “The Secretary of Transportation, acting through the Maritime Administrator, shall engage in the study” for “The Secretary of Transportation may engage in the environmental study”."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Subsec. (b). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/116/92/s3503/2"},"text":"Pub. L. 116–92, § 3503(2)","children":[],"tail":", in introductory provisions of par. (1), substituted “shall identify, study, evaluate, test, demonstrate, or improve emerging marine technologies and practices to improve—” for “may—” and “environmental performance to meet United States Federal and international standards and guidelines, including—” for “(1) identify, study, evaluate, test, demonstrate, or improve emerging marine technologies and practices that are likely to achieve environmental improvements by—”, in subpar. (C) of par. (1), substituted “species; or” for “species; and”, added subpar. (D) of p